title: PML-N’s Aoun Hameed wins PP-271 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz’s (PML-N) candidate Muhammad Aoun Hameed has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-271, Muzaffargarh-IV by securing 29,200 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Mian Muhammad Imran, an independent candidate who bagged 27,426 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 54.07%.
